## Notes
- This is a PROJECT-level verification tool (different from `aimgr repo verify`)
- The `--fix` flag removes broken symlinks but doesn't fully reinstall (users run `aimgr install` after)
- Checks manifest sync to find resources that should be installed but aren't
- Only checks aimgr-managed resources (symlinks pointing to repo)

## Description
Create a new `aimgr clean` command that removes ALL installed symlinks from tool directories (`.claude/`, `.opencode/`, `.github/skills/`, etc.) without modifying ai.package.yaml. This provides a safe way to "start fresh" and reinstall from manifest.

## Purpose
- Remove all aimgr-managed symlinks in one command
- Don't touch ai.package.yaml (so `aimgr install` can restore)
- Safer than `aimgr uninstall` without args (which we're removing)
- Useful for troubleshooting and CI/CD workflows

